{% comment %}
First we are going to capture the user's language and assign it to a variable
The variable name is user_language
We use custom_attribute.language to capture the user language
If the language is not specified we will use as default Es = Spanish
{% endcomment %}
{% assign user_language = custom_attribute.language | default: 'es' %}

{% comment %}
We will use 'if-elseif-endif' condition to evaluate the user language
If the user language = 'Spanish' we will send the message in Spanish
If the user language = 'English' we will send the message in English
{% endcomment %}
{% if user_language == 'es' %}
  ¡Hola {{${first_name} | default: ''}}! aquí tienes los mejores descuentos en {{${city} | default: 'tu zona'}}.
   Disfruta a lo grande desde casa, pagando menos. Pide un Glovo
{% elsif user_language == 'en' %}
  Hello {{${first_name} | default: ''}}! here you have the best discounts in {{${city} | default: 'your area'}}.
   Enjoy a great time from home, paying less. Order a Glovo
{% endif %}

{% comment %}
Furthermore, we will use the tag {first_name} to personalize the email.
If first_name doesn´t exist we will use as default ''. It will see as "¡Hola!"
To personalize as much as possible, we will use the tag {city} to show users that
we care about presenting them with the best personalised offers for them.

{% endcomment %}